solution:
Triangle $ABC$ has base $AB$ of length $25\text{ cm}$ and height $AC$ of length $20\text{ cm}.$ Therefore, the area of triangle $ABC$ is \begin{align*}
\frac{1}{2}bh &= \frac{1}{2}(25 \mbox{ cm})(20 \mbox{ cm}) \\
&= \frac{1}{2}(500 \mbox{ cm}^2) \\
&= \boxed{250} \mbox{ cm}^2.
\end{align*}

Recall that $(-a)^n=-a^n$ when $n$ is odd so we can rewrite $(-5)^5$ as $-5^5$. Because $a^m\div a^n=a^{m-n}$ for positive integers $m>n$, we get $$-5^5\div5^3=-5^{5-3} =-5^2.$$ Now we can rewrite the expression to get  \begin{align*}
(-5)^5\div5^3+3^{4}-6^{1}&=-5^2+3^4-6\\
&=-25+81-6\\
&=\boxed{50}.
\end{align*}

