In cylindrical coordinates, $\theta$ denotes the angle a point makes with the positive $x$-axis.  Thus, for a fixed angle $\theta = c,$ all the points lie on a plane.  The answer is $\boxed{\text{(C)}}.$  Note that we can obtain all points in this plane by taking $r$ negative.

