Find the value of $a$ so that the lines with the given equations are perpendicular. \begin{align*}
y &= 2x+13 \\
6y+ax &= 6.
\end{align*}

solution:
Note that given complex numbers $a$ and $b$ in the plane, there are two complex numbers $c$ such that $a,$ $b,$ and $c$ form an equilateral triangle.  They are shown as $c_1$ and $c_2$ below.

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair A, B;
pair[] C;

A = (2,-1);
B = (0,0);
C[1] = rotate(60,B)*(A);
C[2] = rotate(60,A)*(B);

